[An update on dengue situation in New Caledonia, based on the last report
from New Caledonia Health Department. Thanks to them for sharing this
information -- TK]
The weekly number of reported new cases of dengue situation seems on the
rise again. As usually, majority of the reported new cases are from Noumea
and areas not far from the city (including Mont-Dore, Dumbea and Paita).
Since 28 December 1998, all reported cases with the type of dengue
confirmed [are dengue 2 virus infections], i.e., 184 of 279 reported cases.
No other type of dengue was found. Eight cases were hospitalised. Two cases
were dengue haemorrhagic fevers.
Weekly number of clinical new cases (including the confirmed ones) from the
week starting on 28 December 98 (week 53 of 1999) to the week starting on
22 March 99 (week 12 of 1999) is shown hereunder:
*******************************************
Year Week Number of reported new cases of dengue
____ ____ __________________________________
1998 53 6
1999 1 5
2 9
3 14
4 11
5 26
6 10
7 22
8 38
9 57
10 41
11 29
12 11
Note: the number of reported cases for the last weeks is incomplete.
*******************************************************************
Health authorities are applying perifocal vector control measures including
insecticide spraying and reduction of mosquito breeding sites. Awareness
campaigns targeting at both the public and health professionals are also
conducted.
